msgstr ""

#: src/0069-ascii-literals.md:92
msgid ""
"This RFC was written to align the syntax with Python, but there could be "
"many variations such as using a different prefix (maybe `a` for ASCII), or "
"using a suffix instead (maybe `u8`, as in integer literals)."
msgstr ""

#: src/0069-ascii-literals.md:96
msgid ""
"The code points from syntax could be encoded as UTF-8 rather than being "
"mapped to bytes of the same value, but assuming UTF-8 is not always "
"appropriate when working with bytes."
msgstr ""

